<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
According to the available data, 
<taxonomicName authority="insignitus" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. insignitus subsp. insignitus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="insignitus" subSpecies="insignitus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. insignitus insignitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Morocco (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution of species from subgenus Platyderus Eremoderus in continental North Africa and the southern Levant: Platyderus brunneus brunneus (blue circles), P. brunneus ferrantei (yellow circles), P. insignitus insignitus (red circles), and P. insignitus presaharensis (brown circle)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.83840.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/695655" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">18</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Antoine, M" journalOrPublisher=", Zoologie)" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="179 - 314" refId="B5" refString="Antoine, M, 1957. Coleopteres carabiques du Maroc (deuxieme partie). Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc (N.S., Zoologie) 3: 179 - 314" title="Coleopteres carabiques du Maroc (deuxieme partie). Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc (N. S." volume="3" year="1957">Antoine (1957</bibRefCitation>
: 236) stated that it is a sublittoral species living in the area between Oum er Rbia River to the north and the Anti-Atlas Mountain Range to the south. 
<bibRefCitation author="Machard, P" journalOrPublisher="Coleopterist" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="101 - 102" refId="B36" refString="Machard, P, 2017. Un Platyderus nouveau du Maroc (Coleoptera, Carabidae). Coleopterist 20 (2): 101 - 102" title="Un Platyderus nouveau du Maroc (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="20" year="2017">Machard (2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Machard, P" journalOrPublisher="Coleopterist" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="183 - 203" refId="B37" refString="Machard, P, 2019. Catalogue des Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc (Coleoptera, Carabidae). Coleopterist 21 (3): 183 - 203" title="Catalogue des Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="21" year="2019">2019</bibRefCitation>
) noted that it inhabits the &quot;Littoral atlantique de Casablanca 
<normalizedToken originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
Agadir&quot;. The new data from the environs of Tiznit show that the species occurs south of the city of Agadir as well.
</paragraph>
